Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{12%ounce} on a diagonal into 1⁄2-inch-thick pieces. Toss on one side of a lightly oiled #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @cooking oil{}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack for ~{9%minutes} (you'll add more to the sheet then).

> For 4, spread out across entire sheet and roast on middle rack.

Cut @broccoli{8%ounce} into bite-size pieces if necessary or trim and halve Brussels sprouts lengthwise.

> Save carrots for another use. Swap in broccoli or Brussels sprouts for carrots. Skip roasting in this step; you'll cook them in a later step.

Dice @potatoes{12%ounce} into 1⁄2-inch pieces. Roughly chop @parsley{1/4%ounce}.

Place potatoes in a #medium pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil and cook until tender, ~{10-12%minutes}. Reserve 1⁄4 cup potato cooking liquid (1⁄2 cup for 4 servings), then drain.

Return potatoes to pot and cover to keep warm.

> You'll finish the potatoes in Step 5.

While potatoes cook, in a #large bowl{}, combine @ground beef{10%ounce}, @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}, @brown sugar bourbon seasoning{1}, @garlic powder{1%teaspoon}, and half the parsley. Season with @salt{1/2%tsp} and @pepper{}.

> We used 1 tsp salt for 4 servings.

Form beef mixture into 8-10 1-inch meatballs (16-20 meatballs for 4).

Once carrots have roasted 9 minutes, remove baking sheet from oven. Carefully arrange meatballs on empty side of sheet.

> For 4, leave carrots roasting; add meatballs to a second lightly oiled baking sheet and roast on top rack.

Return sheet to top rack until meatballs are browned and cooked through and carrots are tender, ~{14-16%minutes}.

> Roast broccoli or Brussels sprouts with meatballs as instructed. If meatballs are done before broccoli or Brussels sprouts, carefully remove from sheet and return broccoli or Brussels sprouts to oven for a few more minutes until browned and tender.

In a second large bowl, combine @BBQ sauce{4%tablespoon}, @Dijon mustard{2%teaspoon}, @ketchup{1}, and @warm water{1%tbsp}.

Once carrots and meatballs are done roasting, carefully transfer meatballs to bowl with BBQ glaze; toss to coat. Set aside until ready to serve.

To pot with potatoes, add @sour cream{3%tablespoon} and @butter{2%tbsp}. Mash with a #potato masher{} until smooth and creamy, adding splashes of reserved potato cooking liquid as needed.

Divide meatballs, mashed potatoes, and carrots between plates in separate sections.

Spoon any remaining BBQ glaze over meatballs. Garnish with remaining parsley and serve.

> Ground Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.